w canvas bag  Shredded Paper  collect shredded paper in a separate clear plastic bag  Cardboard YES Broken down corrugated cardboard of any weight Pizza boxes  some staining okay Tape and staples are okay  NO Food  Packing materials Discard or recycle packing materials as appropriate  Flatten boxes and stack at your nearest recycling station  Bottles   Cans   all in the same container YES Plastic bottles Rigid plastic food containers  please scrape or rinse away food  spoon clean  is okay  Aluminum cans  foil and trays Tin cans Empty aerosol cans All colors of glass bottles and jars NO Caps or lids Liquids Food Plastic bags or wrappers Plastic utensils Styrofoam Waxed cartons Disposable coffee cups Remove lids or caps and place in landfill trash Scrape or rinse away food  spoon clean  is okay  Place all containers in a blue bin or a clear plastic bag Batteries All types are accepted Set up a collection box in your office When it is full  call Physical Plant to arrange a pick up Ink and Toner Cartridges All types are accepted Set up a collection box in your office When it is full  call Physical Plant to arrange a pick up VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 